FBIS4-41614 "drsov123_e_94005" FBIS-SOV-94-123 Daily Report 26 Jun 1994 UKRAINE International Affairs Kravchuk Welcomes EU Funds To Shut Down Chernobyl Kravchuk Welcomes EU Funds To Shut Down Chernobyl LD2606225094 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 1900 GMT 26 Jun 94 LD2606225094 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service Ukrainian BFN [Text] The problem of the Chernobyl AES [Nuclear Electric Power Station] is of exceptional importance not only for Ukraine but also for the entire world. This is why we welcome the decision by a session of the European Union council [word indistinct] to allocate 500 million ECU's to implement the plan to completely shut down the Chernobyl AES. It is important to check this amount continuously. This was how Ukrainian President Leonid Kravchuk commented on the decision by a session of the European Union council. He said that, it was first necessary to resolve the issue of [words indistinct]. At the moment, we do not yet know how much will be needed in order to resolve the fate of the Chernobyl AES, Kravchuk stressed.
